reviews.review_text: Magical Show I had a grateful time at these shows with this being the highlight.It seemed like the dead were playing with the weather as though they manipulated it through music.Clear and bright for awhile ,they break dark swirling squalls, come back gorgeous ,space threatening clouds and wind,then they drove it away again to finish with a beautiful late summer evening.It was a blast. My friends knew this older head with the Hog Farm I was dancing around shooting the breeze with him,and he grabbed my arm and is pointing to the sound board and telling "See that guy  next to Healy thats Bear"I said "huh" He said"You know Owsley".I said"Wow,these are mighty good shrooms."But after the last encore everybody in our little section was thanking each other for being there and contributing to the magic.I liked it.Oh yeah,The Oade Bros. made fine recording. To The Highest!
